Military operations in Zamfara State against banditry, have paraded eight suspected informants, including the vice chairman of Anka local government council, Yahuza Ibrahim. Briefing newsmen on the activities of Operation Sharan Daji and Operation Harmin Kunama 111, Force Commander, Major General Hakeem Otiki, said four bandits were neutralised during the operation. Otiki, who spoke through, Major Clement, said additional military personnel have been deployed to the state for the operation Harbin Kunama. According to him, military personnel have been deployed to various locations for engagement. He reiterated the determination of the soldiers involved in the operation to crush the bandits. Otiki however, solicited for more support and cooperation from the general public, especially, in intelligence gathering, to facilitate the war against banditry.